                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400615-name-1245" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400615-name-1245" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400615-name-1245" type="surname" value="ARCHER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400615-name-1245" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN ARCHER</persName>
                  </hi>(<hi rend="italic">police-constable C</hi>150.) I was at Greenwich fair on the 10th of June, in plain clothes—I saw the prisoner, and watched him for</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184006150248"></xptr>
               <p>about twenty minutes—I saw him attempt several person's pockets—I kept my eye on him, and saw him go behind a gentleman, and draw from his pocket this handkerchief, which I now produce—I seized him, and told the gentleman to come with me to the station-house—when he got about half-way, he said he would not go any further, and went away—I asked his name and address, he refused to give it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. He asked the gentleman if it was his handkerchief, and he said no. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. No, the gentleman said he had a great mind to trans<lb></lb>port him.</p>
